I see the error you're encountering. In Java, when a class is declared as `public`, the file name must match the class name. Currently, you're trying to define a public class named `AdvancedCodeToPdfConverter` inside a file named `Main.java`, which causes the compilation error.

Let's fix this issue. There are two possible solutions:

## Solution 1: Rename the file to match the class name

You should rename `Main.java` to `AdvancedCodeToPdfConverter.java` to match the public class name.

## Solution 2: Rename the class to match the file name

Alternatively, you can modify the class name to `Main` to match the file name.

Let's go with the second solution to keep the original file name. Here's the corrected code:

