The primary issue in your codebase is a compatibility problem between the iText Core library (version 8.0.4) and the html2pdf module (version 5.0.4). I've made two key changes to fix the issues:

1. Updated the dependencies in pom.xml to explicitly include the required iText modules instead of using the aggregate itext7-core dependency. This ensures that all necessary components are available.

2. Provided an alternative implementation for the HTML to PDF conversion method that uses a different API call that should be compatible with the libraries.

In iText 8, there have been significant changes to the API structure compared to iText 7, which is why the html2pdf module needs careful version matching. The changes I've made ensure that the appropriate dependencies are included and that the conversion method is compatible with the available API.

If this approach still doesn't resolve the issue, you might need to downgrade to iText 7 (which has better compatibility with the html2pdf module) or upgrade to the latest version of html2pdf that's specifically designed for iText 8.

