I'll fix the issue with code formatting when converting files to PDF, while preserving the exact code structure, tabs, and spaces.

## Analysis:
The PDF conversion isn't preserving code formatting exactly as it appears in the source files. This is a critical feature for a code-to-PDF converter, as proper indentation and spacing are essential for code readability.

## Steps:
1. Create a utility class to handle precise code formatting preservation
2. Implement methods to maintain exact whitespace when converting to PDF
3. Update the PDF generation process to use this utility

## Patches:

<llm-patch path="src/main/java/org/example/CodeFormattingPreserver.java" matcher="BeforeAfter">
Create a utility class to preserve exact code formatting
